precis:
Amendments to the COASTAL FISHERIES PROTECTION REGULATIONS which will
require the operators of foreign commercial fishing vessels to obtain a
licence to pass through specific waters off the coast of continental
British Columbia, and in particular, the waters between Vancouver Island or
the Queen Charlotte Island and the mainland.
